<span id="freeTextContainer15285323156286868432">I kept on reading when Aquamarine was finished in the book I have that has both stories. The quote &quot;A real friend believes in you when you don&apos;t believe in yourself...&quot; immediatly struck me. I&apos;ll keep reading. . . . <br/><br/>Two more quotes struck me this afternoon while reading: <br/>&quot;sometimes words spoken are the ones you&apos;ve been afraid to think, but once they&apos;re said aloud there&apos;s no way to make them disappear.&quot;<br/><br/>&quot;...of how hard it was to leave behind the people you loved, even if the life you wanted wasn&apos;t</span>
  <span id="freeText15285323156286868432" style="display:none">I kept on reading when Aquamarine was finished in the book I have that has both stories. The quote "A real friend believes in you when you don't believe in yourself..." immediatly struck me. I'll keep reading. . . . <br /><br />Two more quotes struck me this afternoon while reading: <br />"sometimes words spoken are the ones you've been afraid to think, but once they're said aloud there's no way to make them disappear."<br /><br />"...of how hard it was to leave behind the people you loved, even if the life you wanted wasn't the one they could give you."<br /><br />This book is about three friends- one girl and two brothers. The brothers are ridiculed and the girl is pitied because she has lost their mother. It is about what leads up to their decision to run away and what brings them back to their small town. Enjoyable with some very thought provoking sentences. Very short read.</span>
