<span id="freeTextContainer5850619585477174316"><b>
  <i>&quot;The town of Oak Grove was so far away from the ocean that most people who lived there had never seen a seagull or listened to the whisper of a pink shell.&quot;</i>
</b><br/><br/>3,5 stars<br/><br/>I enjoyed this one a little less than Aquamarine, but it was still a good read. I definitely liked the mermaid elements and the writing, as always with Alice Hoffman&apos;s books. If you&apos;re interested in reading these, I do recommend to try and find a bind up edition, as both tales aren&apos;t too long :)</span>
